VORIN‑Ω: OMNICOM‑WIDE INTERPRETATION MODULE

Unified Interpretation Layer for All Omricon Levels (O1 → O‑Core)

Engineering Specification — Full Technical Document

---

1. Introduction

VORIN‑Ω is the universal interpretation module for the Omricon architecture.
Its purpose is to convert structured human input into deterministic internal representations that can be consumed by all Omricon reasoning layers.

The system replaces natural‑language parsing with a strict four‑field schema:

AREA
PROBLEM
REQUEST
DOMAIN

This schema ensures that all Omricon modules receive consistent, unambiguous, machine‑processable input.

VORIN‑Ω is designed to be:

• deterministic
• domain‑agnostic
• low‑complexity
• failure‑predictable
• cross‑compatible with all O‑levels

---

2. Problem Statement

Natural language input introduces ambiguity, drift, and inconsistent interpretation.
Earlier versions of Omricon relied on linguistic parsing, which caused:

• misinterpretation of intent
• domain confusion
• contradictory reasoning
• unstable outputs
• high failure rates
• unpredictable behaviour across modules

A deterministic system requires deterministic input.

VORIN‑Ω solves this by enforcing a structured input format that removes ambiguity at the source.

